{{Dialogue a-b|Catelyn Stark|Wise men do not make demands from Kings.|Rickard Karstark|Fathers who love their sons do.|Rickard's desire to kill Jaime Lannister.|A Man Without Honor}}

{{Quote|I lost one son, fighting by your son's side. I lost another to the Kingslayer, strangled with a chain. You commit treason because your children are prisoners? I would carve out my heart and offer it to the Father if he would let my sons wake from their graves and step into a prison cell. I don't want your grief, I want my vengeance, and you stole it from me.|'''Rickard''' to [[Catelyn Stark]] on releasing [[Jaime Lannister]]|The Prince of Winterfell}}

{{Quote|It's treason to free your enemies! In war, you ''kill'' your enemies! Did [[Eddard Stark|your father]] not teach you that, boy!?|'''Rickard''' to Robb Stark|Kissed by Fire}}

{{Quote|Leave me to the King. He wants to give me a scolding before he sets me free. That's how he deals with treason. Our King in the North. Or should I call him 'the King who lost the North'?|'''Rickard''' to Brynden Tully|Kissed by Fire}}

{{Quote|Kill me and be cursed. You are no King of mine!|'''Rickard's''' last words to [[Robb Stark]]|Kissed by Fire}}

